 can see the issue! You have a JSON circular reference problem. The VoteOption contains a Poll, which contains VoteOptions, which contains the same Poll again, creating an infinite loop.
The Problem:

Your VoteOption has a reference to Poll, and Poll has a list of VoteOptions. This creates a circular reference that Jackson (JSON serializer) can't handle.
Solution: Add @JsonIgnore annotations

In your Poll.java, add these imports and annotations:
java

import com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.JsonIgnore;
import com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.JsonManagedReference;
import com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.JsonBackReference;

public class Poll {
    // ... other fields ...
    
    @JsonManagedReference // This manages the forward part of the relationship
    private List<VoteOption> voteOptions = new ArrayList<>();
    
    @JsonBackReference // This handles the back reference
    private List<Vote> votes = new ArrayList<>();
    
    // ... getters and setters ...
}

In your VoteOption.java, add:
java

import com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.JsonBackReference;

public class VoteOption {
    // ... other fields ...
    
    @JsonBackReference // This prevents serialization of the poll back reference
    private Poll poll;
    
    // ... getters and setters ...
}

In your Vote.java, add:
java

import com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.JsonBackReference;

public class Vote {
    // ... other fields ...
    
    @JsonBackReference
    private User user;
    
    @JsonBackReference  
    private VoteOption voteOption;
    
    // ... getters and setters ...
}

Alternative Simpler Solution:

If the above doesn't work, use simple @JsonIgnore:

Poll.java:
java

public class Poll {
    // ... other fields ...
    
    @JsonIgnore
    public List<VoteOption> getVoteOptions() {
        return voteOptions;
    }
    
    @JsonIgnore
    public List<Vote> getVotes() {
        return votes;
    }
}

VoteOption.java:
java

public class VoteOption {
    // ... other fields ...
    
    @JsonIgnore
    public Poll getPoll() {
        return poll;
    }
}

Vote.java:
java

public class Vote {
    // ... other fields ...
    
    @JsonIgnore
    public User getUser() {
        return user;
    }
    
    @JsonIgnore
    public VoteOption getVoteOption() {
        return voteOption;
    }
}

After adding these annotations:

    Restart your application

    Test the vote options endpoint again

    The JSON should now be clean without circular references

The circular reference was causing the infinite nesting in your JSON response! ðŸš€
